{"title":"Macworld readers pick Apple CEO Tim Cookâ€™s successor","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/342867/macworld-readers-pick-apple-ceo-tim-cooks-successor.html","date":1618060692000,"content":"\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section><p>In a recent interview with Kara Swisher on the â€œ<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/04/05/opinion/apples-ceo-is-making-very-different-choices-than-mark-zuckerberg.html&amp;xcust=1-1-342432-0-0-0%7Cxid:fr1617918006770fcf&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/article/342432/tim-cook-not-planning-on-staying-with-apple-through-the-decade.html\">Sway</a>â€ podcast, Apple CEO Tim CookÂ <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/342432/tim-cook-not-planning-on-staying-with-apple-through-the-decade.html\">revealed</a>Â that he doesnâ€™t think heâ€™ll be the head of Apple in 10 years. So with that in mind, we posted this poll on our Twitter feed to you, dear reader: Who do you think should be Cookâ€™s successor? And here are the results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>OK, we know Tim Cook isn't retiring for a while, but if he was, who do you think should be his successor?</p>â€” Macworld (@macworld) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/macworld/status/1380250069870465025?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>Federighi finishes first</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Senior VPÂ <a href=\"https://apple.sjv.io/c/321564/435031/7613?u=https://www.apple.com/leadership/craig-federighi/&amp;subid1=1-1-342867-0-0-0\">Craig Federighi</a>Â was the top choice in the poll and thatâ€™s not surprising. Of all of Appleâ€™sÂ <a href=\"https://apple.sjv.io/c/321564/435031/7613?u=https://www.apple.com/leadership/&amp;subid1=1-1-342867-0-0-0\">leaders</a>, Federighi is the most recognized by Apple users and fans. He has taken over the mantle of showmanship during Apple events, able to combine enthusiasm, intelligence, humor, and charm in performances that are must-see. Plus he seems like a really great guy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>It definitely should be someone who knows Apple inside out and Craig is that. Plus, he looks the part for being the face of Apple and he knows how to present product info clearly and in depth. The CEO has a board of advisors and underlings that handle all the biz details</p>â€” Lauri Mueller (@LauriLinnea) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/LauriLinnea/status/1380619054432583684?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 9, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>He is the best one <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://t.co/TRaxl0T2RE&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">https://t.co/TRaxl0T2RE</a></p>â€” IB Putu Arim Pranata (@arimpranata) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/arimpranata/status/1380848000331702277?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 10, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Heâ€™s a great guy. Wrote to him about a really low level cryptography question regarding the macOS kernel and got a response.</p>â€” John Woods (@JohnAlanWoods) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/JohnAlanWoods/status/1380609259260551171?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 9, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><p>However, not everyone was on board with Hair Force One as CEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Craig was too obvious.<br /><br />Though as charismatic as he is, and heâ€™s been a key asset in keeping the Mac alive during these dark times, would he even make a good CEO? Heâ€™s a great presenter and software engineer. Leaderâ€¦thatâ€™s another story</p>â€” Spaceboi Scaphandre ğŸ”ï£¿ Help Iâ€™m trapped in FFXIV (@Dr_Scaphandre) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Dr_Scaphandre/status/1380609164536348676?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 9, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>No to COO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The main reason Federighi got the most votes is that heâ€™s a successful leader of Appleâ€™s OS development, and many Apple fans and our readers would like to see a â€œproductâ€ person lead the company again. Thatâ€™s probably why Chief Operating OfficerÂ <a href=\"https://apple.sjv.io/c/321564/435031/7613?u=https://www.apple.com/leadership/jeff-williams/&amp;subid1=1-1-342867-0-0-0\">Jeff Williams</a>Â did poorly in our pollâ€”despite the fact that Cook himself was COO before becoming CEO. Some of our readers appreciated that fact.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>But the current CEO's preference should be for Jeff Williams. Both apparently have very similar characteristics and personalities. But I am not convinced that it would be the best option.</p>â€” _asfonseca ğŸ˜·ğŸ’‰ (@_asfonseca) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/_asfonseca/status/1380256054672551942?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I concur. Jeff Williams is the most probable successor.</p>â€” iHadrami ï£¿ (@iHadrami_) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/iHadrami_/status/1380258676443918340?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>Joz needs to market himself better</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Surprisingly, Senior VPÂ <a href=\"https://apple.sjv.io/c/321564/435031/7613?u=https://www.apple.com/leadership/greg-joswiak/&amp;subid1=1-1-342867-0-0-0\">Greg â€œJozâ€ Jozwiak</a>Â finished last in our poll. Thatâ€™s not because heâ€™s incapable of the job, but more likely that the people who voted in our poll arenâ€™t that familiar with him. He replacedÂ Phil SchillerÂ lastÂ August and has recently been more present during Apple events. Another reason he didnâ€™t do well in our poll: heâ€™s a marketing guy, not a â€œproductâ€ guy, and as I mentioned before, Macworld readers have a preference for product people.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Federighi is popular because of his charismatic personality, but he is a technician and not a business executive. From this list, the best options are, without a doubt, Joswiak and Williams. I would prefer Joswiak, he seems to be more daring and has a more expansive personality.</p>â€” _asfonseca ğŸ˜·ğŸ’‰ (@_asfonseca) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/_asfonseca/status/1380254878371614724?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>The walking dead</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Zombie Steve Jobs got the second-most votes in our poll, and weâ€™re not surprised. When thereâ€™s a joke answer in a poll, some people will pick it, regardless of what they really believe. (Iâ€™m guilty of doing that.) But thereâ€™s a sizeable section of Appleâ€™s fan base that is devoted to Steve Jobs, and a vote here is symbolic of that devotion. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Or you really, really want a zombie Steve Jobs as CEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, we were trying to be funny, but some of you took exception to our suggestion that a waking dead man could run the most powerful company in the world. Which goes to show that we here at Macworld should just stick to providing helpful and insightful content and stay away from the business of deciding the companyâ€™s next leader.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Wow that's bad taste</p>â€” Benj Edwards (@benjedwards) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/benjedwards/status/1380250489770622978?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>\"Zombie Steve Jobs\"? Seriously?</p>â€” TÎ›RÎ›S (@TarasBuria) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/TarasBuria/status/1380261773970968587?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>Other possible candidates</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Some readers had other suggestions on the next CEO. All of these â€œcandidatesâ€ were alive at the time of this writing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Ternus</p>â€” tweeted: (@innovationsdead) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/innovationsdead/status/1380251316757393411?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Scott Forstall</p>â€” Egil (@xep97) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/xep97/status/1380263264555311112?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>The person who designed the much maligned iPod Touch.  All the functionality of an iPhone without the annoying ringing.</p>â€” W.L. Lewis (@ArtMusicLife) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/ArtMusicLife/status/1380252560494374913?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>The four children, Reed Paul, Eve Jobs, Erin Sienna, &amp; Lisa Brennan-Jobs.</p>â€” Pensiveâ„¢ ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ğŸ’¯ğŸ”¥ğŸŒ¹ğŸ’š (@PensiveTM) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/PensiveTM/status/1380253368396963842?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Nobody wanted to consider Kevin Lynch? Led the team that developed Apple Watch.</p>â€” Connor Duffus (@masterduffus) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/masterduffus/status/1380644900929208324?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 9, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>5 â€“ 10 years down the road, Lisa Jackson could maybe also be a possible candidate.</p>â€” Jakob E Hansen ğŸŒˆ (@jakobesben) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/jakobesben/status/1380794545395339266?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 10, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><p>Finally, no list of candidates would be complete without an obligatory mention of the second-most popular Apple person ever.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Steve Wozniak</p>â€” Maf Vosburgh (@MafVosburgh) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/MafVosburgh/status/1380250622709035009?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342867-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">April 8, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><p><strong>Update 4/10:</strong> <em>Added more of your tweets, thanks Macworld readers!</em></p>\n</div>","author":"Roman Loyola","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"0211edbb48130b3f8073a6169f0b5ba54154e9